uientry.unicode: Help||This will take you to the in-game encyclopaedia.
When this timer runs out, the battle will be fought according to the default setting. || The default setting is the button that is highlighted.
Once you have captured a settlement, you need to decide what to do with it.||Mouse over the sections below for more details.

state.unicode: Looting will damage all buildings within the castle town and will have a negative effect on the daimyo's honour.

uientry.unicode: Looting a settlement will provide a lot of money in the short term, but it will damage more buildings and public order will be worse, making it harder to keep control of the settlement.
uientry.s:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("settlement_captured"))
function EmbeddedOnMouseLClickUp() parent :LuaCall("LootSettlement") end

uientry.unicode: Looting will provide more money than peaceful occupation, but may also damage buildings and negatively affect public order in the province.

state.unicode: Peaceful occupation will result in minor damage to military buildings within the castle town.

uientry.unicode: Peaceful occupation gives less money than looting, but fewer buildings will be damaged and public order will be better, making it easier to keep control of the settlement and develop it.
uientry.s:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("settlement_captured"))
function EmbeddedOnMouseLClickUp() parent :LuaCall("OccupySettlement") end

uientry.unicode: Peaceful occupation gives less money than looting, but fewer buildings will be damaged and public order will be better, making it easier to keep control of the settlement and develop it.

state.unicode: In making this clan a vassal, they will receive your protection in return for a regular tribute and free reign over their territory.
As a mark of respect for their new masters, the vassal will provide your clan with one military unit.

uientry.unicode: If this was the last settlement of this clan, you can give them a stay of execution by making them a vassal clan.||This means they receive protection from you in return for a regular payment and full access to their lands.
uientry.s:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("settlement_captured"))
function EmbeddedOnMouseLClickUp() parent :LuaCall("LiberateSettlement") end

uientry.unicode: If this was the last settlement of this clan, you can give them a stay of execution by making them a vassal clan.||This means they receive protection from you in return for a regular payment and full access to their lands.
